The paper deals with a scheduling problem with precedence constraints, which is a classic topic in computer science. The problem is related to optimization and approximation algorithms, which are often studied in the cs.DS and cs.DM sub-categories. The paper also presents structural insights and polynomial-time algorithms, which are relevant to the cs.CC and cs.GT sub-categories. Finally, the problem can be seen as a variant of the resource-constrained project scheduling problem, which is a well-known problem in artificial intelligence and operations research, hence the cs.AI sub-category is also relevant.
